    "FOUR Churchill Places British Seal of Approval on Fascism FRIENDSHIP OF NATIONS TOPIC OF INTERVIEW Mussolini Praised for Services to World CHICAGO Winston Churchill chancellor of the British exchequer yesterday placed the seal of the British governments approval on Fascism In behalf of Great Brit ain he thanked Premier Benito Mussolini for his services to the world in combating the Russian poison This was the substance of an interview handed to repre sentatives of the Italian anl foreign press at the British embassy ac cording to a copyrighted Rome story in The Tribune Owing to the joint responsibility of the British government for the declarations of any of its ministers Mr Churchills statements are of utmost importance in international relations He spoke of the friend ship between Italy and Great Brit ain as one which has existed since the foundation of the United Italian state andwhich never has been dis turbed Reveals His Talks He advised the Italian finance ministry by implication that sta bilization and a return to the gold standard would be a highly satis factory course Mr Churchills statement revealed In a large measure the nature of his talks with Sig Mussolini and Finance Minister Volpi He"
